<h2>4 · Count the Length 🔢</h2>
<p>Counting squares has a trap. From <strong>X = 2</strong> to <strong>X = 5</strong> is <strong>not</strong> 5 squares — it is <strong>2, 3, 4, 5 = 4 squares</strong>. You count the START square too.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Length = (END − START) + 1.</strong>
So to make a line <strong>N</strong> long starting at X, the END is <strong>X + (N − 1)</strong> — not X + N.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>You want a line lying down that is 3 squares long, starting at X = 1 (Y stays 2). What is the END X?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Now write the fill for it — blocks or python, your choice:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>You want a line standing up, 5 squares tall, starting at Y = 0 (X stays 6). What is the END Y?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

