<h2>5 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each command was meant to do one thing, but it is wrong. Rewrite it so it works, then explain why the original was wrong.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — Meant to color <strong>one</strong> square at X 4, Y 4.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">blocks.fill(RED_WOOL, world(4, 4, 0), world(5, 5, 0), FillOperation.Replace)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> count how many squares <code>(4,4)</code> to <code>(5,5)</code> really covers.</p>
